        <subsection xml:id="subsec-bounds"><title>Upper and lower bound properties of ‚Ñï and ‚Ñù</title>

          <definition xml:id="def-1.39">
            <statement>
              <p>
                <ol>
                  <li>
                    <p>
                      An <em>upper bound</em> for a subset <m>A ‚äÜ ‚Ñù</m> is a real number <m>r ‚àà ‚Ñù</m> satisfying <m>a ‚â§ r</m> for all <m>a ‚àà A</m>. 
                    </p>
                  </li>

                  <li>
                    <p>
                      A <em>lower bound</em> for a subset <m>A ‚äÜ ‚Ñù</m> is a real number <m>s ‚àà ‚Ñù</m> satisfying <m>s ‚â§ a</m> for all <m>a ‚àà A</m>.
                    </p>
                  </li>
                </ol>
              </p>
            </statement>
          </definition>

          <definition xml:id="def-1.40">
            <statement>
              <p>
                <ol>
                  <li>
                    <p>
                      (Least upper bound property of <m>‚Ñù</m>): If <m>A ‚äÜ ‚Ñù</m> and <m>A</m> has an upper bound, then <m>A</m> has a least upper bound. 
