                    </p>
                  </li>

                  <li>
                    <p>
                      Finite complement topology on a set <m>X: ùíØ_{fc} := \{U ‚äÜ X | X - U is a finite set\} ‚à™ \{‚àÖ\}</m>.
                    </p>
                  </li>

                  <li>
                    <p>
                      Included point topology on a set <m>X</m> with included point <m>a ‚àà X: ùíØ_{incl} := \{U ‚äÜ X | a ‚àà U\} ‚à™ \{‚àÖ\}</m>.
                    </p>
                  </li>

                  <li>
                    <p>
                      Excluded point topology on a set <m>X</m> with excluded point <m>a ‚àà X: ùíØ_{excl} := \{U ‚äÜ X | a ‚àâ U\} ‚à™ \{X\}</m>.
                    </p>
                  </li>

                  <li>
                    <p>
                      Infinite ray topology on <m>‚Ñù: ùíØ_{ray} := \{ (-‚àû,a) | a ‚àà ‚Ñù\} ‚à™ \{‚àÖ,‚Ñù\}</m>.
                    </p>
                  </li>

                  <li>
                    <p>
                      Preimage topology constructed on a set <m>X</m> from a function <m>f:X ‚Üí Y</m> and a topology <m>ùíØ_Y</m> on <m>Y: ùíØ_f := \{f-1(U) | U ‚àà ùíØY\}</m>.
                    </p>
                  </li>

                  <li>
                    <p>
                      Line with two origins with set <m>(‚Ñù - \{0\}) ‚à™ \{*,@\}</m> and topology <m>ùíØ := \{U | U ‚äÜ ‚Ñù,- \{0\} and U ‚àà ùíØEucl\} ‚à™ \{(U - \{0\}) ‚à™ \{*\} | U ‚äÜ ‚Ñù, 0 ‚àà U, and U ‚àà ùíØEucl\} ‚à™ \{(U - \{0\}) ‚à™ \{@\} | U ‚äÜ ‚Ñù, 0 ‚àà U, and U ‚àà ùíØEucl\} ‚à™ \{(U - \{0\}) ‚à™ \{*,@\} | U ‚äÜ ‚Ñù, 0 ‚àà U, and U ‚àà ùíØEucl\}</m>.
                    </p>
                  </li>

                  <li>
                    <p>
                      On the finite set <m>X = \{a,b,c\}: ùíØ = \{ ‚àÖ, \{a\}, \{a,b\}, \{a,c\}, X\}</m>.
                    </p>
                  </li>
                </ol>                
              </p>
            </statement>
           
          </example>

          <lemma xml:id="lem-2.7">
            <statement>
              <p>
                All of the examples in <xref ref="def-2.6"/> are topologies.
              </p>
            </statement>
          </lemma>

          <definition xml:id="def-2.9">
            <statement>
              <p>
                Let <m>ùíØ</m> and <m>ùíØ'</m> be topologies on a set <m>X</m>. If <m>ùíØ ‚äÜ ùíØ</m>, then the topology <m>ùíØ</m> is called smaller or coarser than <m>ùíØ'</m>, and the topology <m>ùíØ'</m> is called larger or finer than <m>ùíØ</m>.
              </p>
            </statement>
