          </theorem>

          <theorem xml:id="thm-2.139">
            <statement>
              <p>
                Let Z be a topological space, let A be an open set in Z, and let ‚àº be an equivalence relation on Z satisfying the property that for each a ‚àà A, the equivalence class of a satisfies [a] = \{a\}. If A has the subspace topology and Z/‚àº has the quotient topology, then the function g: A ‚Üí Z/‚àº defined by g(a) := [a] for all a ‚àà A is an embedding.
