            </statement>
          </theorem>

          <theorem xml:id="thm-2.142">
            <statement>
              <p>
                Let X be a topological space, let ‚àº be an equivalence relation on X, and let q:X ‚Üí X/‚àº be the quotient map. Let A be a subspace of X and let q(A) have the subspace topology in X/‚àº.
                <ol>
                  <li>
                    <p>
                      The relation ‚âà on A defined by [a ‚âà a' if and only if a ‚àº a' for all a,a' ‚àà A] is an equivalence relation on A.
                    </p>
                  </li>

                  <li>
                    <p>
                      If A = q-1(q(A)) and A is either an open or closed subset of X, then the the function q|Aq(A):A ‚Üí q(A) is a quotient map and the function h: A/‚âà ‚Üí q(A) defined by h([a]) := [h(a)] for all [a] ‚àà A/‚âà is a homeomorphism.
                    </p>
