      <section xml:id="sec-closed"><title>Closed sets, boundaries, and continuity</title>

        <subsection xml:id="subsec-closed"><title>Closed sets</title>

          <definition xml:id="def-2.150">
            <statement>
              <p>
                A subset C of a topological space X is a <em>closed set</em> in X if and only if X - C is open in X.
              </p>
            </statement>
          </definition>

          <theorem xml:id="thm-2.151">
            <statement>
              <p>
                Let X be a topological space. Then 
                (1) 
                ‚àÖ and X are closed in X; 
                (2) 
                whenever AŒ± is closed in X for all Œ±, then ‚à©Œ± AŒ± is closed in X; and 
