              </p>
            </statement>
          </theorem>

        </subsection>

        <subsection xml:id="subsec-closures"><title>Closures, interiors, boundaries, and limit points</title>

          <definition xml:id="def-2.170">
            <statement>
              <p>
                Let X be a topological space and let A ‚äÜ X.
                The <em>closure</em> of A in X is the set ClX(A) := ‚à©A ‚äÜ C ‚äÜ X, C closed in X C.
                The <em>interior</em> of A in X is the set IntX(A) := ‚à™U ‚äÜ A, U open in X U.
                The <em>boundary</em> of A in X is BdX(A) := ClX(A) ‚à© ClX(X-A).
