              </p>
            </statement>
          </theorem>

          <theorem xml:id="thm-2.182">
            <statement>
              <p>
                Let XŒ± be a topological space and let AŒ± ‚äÜ XŒ± for all Œ±. Let ‚àèŒ± XŒ± have the product topology. Then Cl‚àèŒ± XŒ±(‚àèŒ± AŒ±) = ‚àèŒ± ClXŒ±(AŒ±).
              </p>
            </statement>
          </theorem>

          <theorem xml:id="thm-2.185">
            <statement>
              <p>
                Let (X,ùíØ) be a topological space, let A ‚äÜ X, and let p ‚àà X. 
                (1) 
                The point p ‚àà ClX(A) if and only if every open set in X that contains p intersects A. 
