              </p>
            </statement>
          </theorem>

          <definition xml:id="def-2.190">
            <statement>
              <p>
                Let X be a topological space, let A ‚äÜ X, and let p ‚àà X. The point p is a <em>limit point</em> of A in X if and only if for every open set U in X containing p, the set (A -\{p\}) ‚à© U ‚â† ‚àÖ. The set of limit points of A in X is denoted LimX(A).
