        </paragraphs>

        <theorem xml:id="thm-3.67">
          <statement>
            <p>
              Let X and Y be topological spaces with X ‚à© Y = ‚àÖ, and let x0 ‚àà X and y0 ‚àà Y. Let Z := X ‚à™ Y have the disjoint union topology. Define ‚àº to be the minimal equivalence relation on Z such that x0 ~ y0, and let Z/‚àº be the corresponding quotient space. Then: 
