                  </p>
                </li>
              </ol>
            </p>
          </statement>
        </lemma>

        <definition xml:id="def-5.10">
          <statement>
            <p>
              Let X be a topological space and let x0 ‚àà X. The fundamental group of X at the basepoint x0, written œÄ1(X,x0), is the set of path homotopy equivalence classes of loops in X at x0, with group operation defined by [f][g] := [f‚àóg] for all [f],[g] ‚àà œÄ1(X,x0).
            </p>
          </statement>
        </definition>

        <theorem xml:id="thm-5.11">
          <statement>
            <p>
              œÄ1(X,x0) is a group.
            </p>
          </statement>
        </theorem>

        <example>
          <p>
            Examples
          </p>
        </example>

        <theorem xml:id="thm-5.13">
          <statement>
