      <section xml:id="sec-group-homs"><title>Group homomorphisms</title>

        <subsection xml:id="subsec-cob"><title>Change of basepoint and PC spaces</title>

          <definition xml:id="def-5.17">
            <statement>
              <p>
                Let p:I ‚Üí X be a path in a space X from x0 to x1. The change of basepoint homomorphism induced by p is the function Œ≤p: œÄ1(X,x0) ‚Üí œÄ1(X,x1) defined by Œ≤p([f]) := [prev‚àóf‚àóp] for all [f] ‚àà œÄ1(X,x0).
              </p>
