        <theorem xml:id="thm-6.88">
          <statement>
            <p>
              Let (X,x0) be a PC, LPC, SLSC space, let G := œÄ1(X,x0), and let p: (XÃÉ,xÃÉ0) ‚Üí (X,x0) be the SC covering. Let r: (Z,z0) ‚Üí (X,x0) be any PC covering space. Then:
              <ol>
                <li><title>Galois Correspondence Thm</title>
                  <p>
                    The maps {subgroups H of G} ‚Üî {isomorphism classes of PC pointed coverings of (X,x0)} defined by
                    H ‚Üí (rH: (XÃÉ/H,[xÃÉ0]H) ‚Üí (X,x0)) and
                    (t: (Y,y0) ‚Üí (X,x0)) ‚Üí Im t‚àó = t‚àó(œÄ1(Y,y0))
                    are inverse bijections.
