                </li>

                <li><title>Action Thm</title>
                  <p>
                    Let H := r‚àó(œÄ1(Z,z0)) and let NG(H) := the normalizer of H in G := { g ‚àà G | gHg-1 ‚äÜ H }. The group of deck transformations of r: Z ‚Üí X is isomorphic to NG(H)/H and has a covering space action on Z. Moreover, (H is normal in G) iff (G/H has a covering space action on Z inducing r) iff (the covering space r:Z ‚Üí X is normal).
                  </p>
                </li>
              </ol>
            </p>
          </statement>
        </theorem>

        <remark>
          <p>
            A Galois correspondence table has columns for spaces, fundamental groups, and covering space group actions. Each row of contains a space X, œÄ1(X), and the (deck transformation) group that acts on X with covering space group action (and is maximal with respect to that property). In the column of spaces, a space Y appears in a row above a space X if there is a covering space : Y ‚Üí X.
