          <paragraphs><title>Another excursion into homological algebra:</title>

            <definition xml:id="def-7.105">
              <statement>
                <p>
                  A sequence of œÜ:A ‚Üí B, Œ∏:B ‚Üí C of groups and homomorphisms is exact at B if Im œÜ = Ker Œ∏. A sequence ‚ãØ Dn+1 ‚Üí Dn ‚Üí ‚ãØ is exact if it is exact at every group.
                </p>
